description: Try this recipe for healthier air-fryer fish and chips. The family will love the sweet potato twist on the crispy fries that go with the herby fish.
keywords: Fish & chips,Air fryer,Low saturated fat,Healthier Easier,Jun 2021,Lemon,Winter,Low sugar,Fakeaway,Fish,High protein,High fibre,Sweet potato,Kale,Autumn
name: Healthier Air-Fryer Fish & Chips Recipe | Woolworths
recipeIngredient: 0.5 bunch continental parsley, leaves picked, finely chopped
400g firm white fish fillets, cut into 3cm-thick strips
2 tbs healthier tartare sauce, to serve

recipeInstructions.text: Preheat air fryer to 200Â°C. Lightly spray potato with oil. Season with pepper. Place potato in air fryer basket and slide into air fryer. Cook for 12 minutes, shaking basket often, or until golden and cooked. Remove basket, transfer potato to a baking tray and cover with foil to keep warm.

Meanwhile, place flour on a plate, place egg in a shallow bowl, and combine breadcrumbs, zest and parsley on a separate plate. Working with one piece of fish at a time, coat in flour, then dip in egg and coat in breadcrumb mixture. Repeat with remaining fish, flour, egg and breadcrumb mixture.
Place fish, in a single layer, in air fryer basket. Spray with oil. Slide basket into air fryer. Cook for 12 minutes, turning fish halfway through cooking, or until golden and just cooked through.
Meanwhile, make kaleslaw according to packet instructions. Serve fish with chips, kaleslaw, tartare sauce and lemon wedges.
